metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #300
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Glyphs #92
metadata.description:
Glyphs attempts to expand upon the seemingly random, yet beautiful forms found in the world around us. They capture the structured randomness in everyday life. 

Inspired by the handwritten form and the spatial complexities of figure ground maps within the urban context.

Glyphs are randomly produced within a set of rules, some more complex than others.

There are 11 color palette options, each containing a number of specific color options.  

Two main graphics options require different compute times. Faded outputs will take longer to render than others. For this reason I have required a 60s view capture to ensure everyone gets a thumbnail regardless of the features.

“S” - save image as .JPG

Glyphs | cmplx 2022 | JPG | 2500x2500

metadata.name: White flags #173
metadata.description:
All I can do for the moment, is give the world some paint-bombs and color explosions. Focus on things you like and love, don't let the hate consume you.


mouse-click: 
- screen scaled image
- full image 3000x3000

The scaled image will reset after some time, with a new drawing
I like it, when you make a work, that will refresh after sometime,
chill out, and see it go.

Tech - Vanilla java-script; a custom build 'soft' 3D-engine.
I can do more things if I can control the (3D) drawing, the color of every pixel.
Also added a z-buffer to the  line-drawing routine this time.
More information in the source-code.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation 00 - special edition #96
metadata.description:
Thank you!

Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 640 special edition generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation 00 is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.
